<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,1070,1421]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1142,1168]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Schweger, S. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Yang, M. - M. &amp; Stone, G. N. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Sinclair, F. &amp; Hearn, J. &amp; Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z." box="[474,741,1142,1169]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref52592" refString="Schweger, S., Melika, G., Tang, C. - T., Yang, M. - M., Stone, G. N., Nicholls, J. A., Sinclair, F., Hearn, J., Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z. (2015 b) New species of cynipid inquilines of the genus Saphonecrus (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Synergini) from the Eastern Palaearctic, with a re-appraisal of known species world-wide. Zootaxa, 4054 (1), 1 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4054.1.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Schwéger 
<emphasis box="[590,639,1142,1168]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. (2015b)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Lobato-Vila, I. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J." box="[793,1087,1142,1169]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref46786" refString="Lobato-Vila, I., Wang, Y., Melika, G., Guo, R., Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. (2021 b) A taxonomic review of the gall wasp genus Saphonecrus Dalla-Torre &amp; Kieffer and other oak cynipid inquilines (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) from mainland China, with updated keys to Eastern Palaearctic and Oriental species. Zoological Studies, 60 (10), 1 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.6620 / ZS. 2021.60 - 10" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lobato-Vila 
<emphasis box="[935,983,1142,1168]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. (2021b)
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melika, Acs &amp; Bechtold" authorityYear="2004" box="[1098,1282,1142,1169]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Saphonecrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chaodongzhui">
<emphasis box="[1098,1282,1142,1169]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. chaodongzhui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded in 
<collectingRegion box="[180,280,1178,1204]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[295,365,1178,1204]" name="China" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">China</collectingCountry>
) by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, Y. &amp; Chen, X. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wu, H. &amp; He, J." box="[415,629,1178,1205]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1034 - 1039" refId="ref55032" refString="Wang, Y., Chen, X., Pujade-Villar, J., Wu, H. &amp; He, J. (2010) The genus Saphonecrus Dalla-Torre &amp; Kieffer, 1910 (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) in China, with descriptions of two new species. Biologia, 65, 1034 - 1039. https: // doi. org / 10.2478 / s 11756 - 010 - 0120 - 9" type="journal article" year="2010">
Wang 
<emphasis box="[487,537,1178,1204]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. (2010)
</bibRefCitation>
. However, this record is erroneous; in 
<collectingCountry box="[1064,1134,1178,1204]" name="China" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melika, Acs &amp; Bechtold" authorityYear="2004" box="[1146,1331,1178,1205]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Saphonecrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chaodongzhui">
<emphasis box="[1146,1331,1178,1205]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. chaodongzhui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been found only in 
<collectingRegion box="[308,394,1215,1241]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, Y. &amp; Chen, X. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wu, H. &amp; He, J." box="[408,605,1214,1241]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1034 - 1039" refId="ref55032" refString="Wang, Y., Chen, X., Pujade-Villar, J., Wu, H. &amp; He, J. (2010) The genus Saphonecrus Dalla-Torre &amp; Kieffer, 1910 (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) in China, with descriptions of two new species. Biologia, 65, 1034 - 1039. https: // doi. org / 10.2478 / s 11756 - 010 - 0120 - 9" type="journal article" year="2010">
Wang 
<emphasis box="[482,531,1214,1240]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,1070,1421]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,306,1250,1276]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Remarks (2).</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hartig" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[312,564,1250,1276]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Saphonecrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connatus">
<emphasis box="[312,564,1250,1276]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Saphonecrus connatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is thought to be a trans-Palaearctic species and was mentioned from 
<collectingCountry box="[1326,1390,1251,1277]" name="Japan" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Japan</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,292,1286,1313]" name="South Korea" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">South Korea</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sakagami, S." box="[307,486,1286,1312]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="112 - 115" refId="ref52440" refString="Sakagami, S. (1949) Notes on Saphonecrus connatus (Hartig) (Hym., Cynipidae). Matsumushi, 3, 112 - 115. [in Japanese]" type="journal article" year="1949">Sakagami 1949</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sakagami, S." box="[497,556,1286,1313]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="67 - 79" refId="ref52473" refString="Sakagami, S. (1952) Zur Cynipoidenfauna Japan und seiner Nachbarlander (Hymenoptera). Mushi, 24, 67 - 79." type="journal article" year="1952">1952</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Abe, Y. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Stone, G. N." box="[567,746,1286,1313]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="169 - 212" refId="ref42072" refString="Abe, Y., Melika, G. &amp; Stone, G. N. (2007) The diversity and phylogeography of cynipid gallwasps (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) of the Oriental and Eastern Palearctic regions, and their associated communities. Oriental Insects, 41 (1), 169 - 212. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00305316.2007.10417504" type="journal article" year="2007">
Abe 
<emphasis box="[621,671,1286,1312]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. 2007
</bibRefCitation>
). However, this record might be well 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melika, Acs &amp; Bechtold" authorityYear="2004" box="[1170,1355,1286,1313]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Saphonecrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chaodongzhui">
<emphasis box="[1170,1355,1286,1313]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. chaodongzhui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a species that is closely related to (and morphologically similar to) 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hartig" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[846,975,1323,1349]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Saphonecrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="connatus">
<emphasis box="[846,975,1323,1349]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">S. connatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Schweger, S. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Yang, M. - M. &amp; Stone, G. N. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Sinclair, F. &amp; Hearn, J. &amp; Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z." box="[1138,1393,1322,1349]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref52592" refString="Schweger, S., Melika, G., Tang, C. - T., Yang, M. - M., Stone, G. N., Nicholls, J. A., Sinclair, F., Hearn, J., Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z. (2015 b) New species of cynipid inquilines of the genus Saphonecrus (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Synergini) from the Eastern Palaearctic, with a re-appraisal of known species world-wide. Zootaxa, 4054 (1), 1 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4054.1.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Schwéger 
<emphasis box="[1255,1305,1322,1348]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. 2015b
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,1070,1421]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,1358,1384]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Biology.</emphasis>
Reared from leaf galls on 
<taxonomicName box="[590,707,1358,1385]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Castanea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="dentata">
<emphasis box="[590,707,1358,1385]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Q. dentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[780,874,1359,1385]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[780,874,1359,1385]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Schweger, S. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Tang, C. - T. &amp; Yang, M. - M. &amp; Stone, G. N. &amp; Nicholls, J. A. &amp; Sinclair, F. &amp; Hearn, J. &amp; Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z." box="[897,1153,1358,1385]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 84" refId="ref52592" refString="Schweger, S., Melika, G., Tang, C. - T., Yang, M. - M., Stone, G. N., Nicholls, J. A., Sinclair, F., Hearn, J., Bozso, M. &amp; Penzes, Z. (2015 b) New species of cynipid inquilines of the genus Saphonecrus (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae: Synergini) from the Eastern Palaearctic, with a re-appraisal of known species world-wide. Zootaxa, 4054 (1), 1 - 84. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4054.1.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Schwéger 
<emphasis box="[1016,1064,1358,1384]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. 2015b
</bibRefCitation>
). The gall inducer has yet to be confirmed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
